type="local"
addr="lmcs">Logical Methods in Computer Science</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We present XTT, a version of Cartesian cubical type theory specialized for Bishop sets à la <fr:link
href="thierrycoquand.xml"
type="local"
addr="thierrycoquand">Coquand</fr:link>, in which every type enjoys a definitional version of the uniqueness of identity proofs. Using cubical notions, XTT reconstructs many of the ideas underlying Observational Type Theory, a version of intensional type theory that supports function extensionality. We prove the canonicity property of XTT (that every closed boolean is definitionally equal to a constant) by Artin gluing.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related><fr:tree
